  "doc_id": "14882",
  "text": "The agent-oriented model-based approach to personalising an individual's interface to the technology in their lives is a natural fit. The mentalistic notions that the AO paradigm abstracts in a computational form, draws upon Psychology, and therefore can be reverse-focused upon programming for individuals, by end-users themselves. The models from cognitive task modeling told us that goals, plans, tasks, actions, roles and objects are represented in the cognitive functioning of the mind. These models confirm those from the agent-oriented paradigm [CITATION_1] , and vice versa, through their strong underlying similarities. And it is the models that will hold POP together as the artifacts shared between the Software Engineers building the toolkits, and the end-users innovating their own creations and customisations with them.",
